The solution iterates through the characters of str1 and checks if the first character of str2 matches the current character of str1. If there is a mismatch, the function returns false, indicating that str2 cannot be a subsequence of str1. If the function reaches the end of str1 without finding a mismatch, it returns true, indicating that str2 can be a subsequence of str1.

